revised_title: A Detailed Analysis of the Presomite Stage Human Embryo (Embryo Dobbin)
tldr: This article presents a detailed study of a human embryo in the presomite stage, known as Embryo Dobbin. The embryo is well-preserved and provides valuable insights into the development of early human embryos. The study focuses on the embryonal shield, yolk-sac vesicle, connecting stalk, and the yolk-sac process. The findings contribute to the understanding of human embryonic development and the role of the yolk-sac process in particular.
